                                <th>Summary</th>
                                <th>Units</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Disk Used Percentage</td>
                                <td>The amount of disk space being used</td>
                                <td>The percentage of total disk space that is currently in use.
                                    High disk usage can indicate that the system is under heavy load,
                                    which may slow down file access and overall system responsiveness and performance.
                                </td>
                                <td>%/GB</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Disk Free</td>
                                <td>The amount of disk space that is free</td>
                                <td>The amount of disk space that is currently not being used.
                                    Sufficient free disk space is important for system performance,
                                    as it allows the system to store new files and data as needed.
                                </td>
                                <td>GB</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
